<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,151,285]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
As outlined by Mah (2011) 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1899" box="[542,652,151,176]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Cladaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[542,652,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Cladaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are known from widely disparate localities but differ by relatively few and/or continuous characters. The most morphologically distinct species in this genus appear geographically discontinuous. It is possible that further sampling might show a widely occurring species as was observed in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mah et al. 2015)" authorityName="Mah" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Mah" baseAuthorityYear="2015" box="[288,627,260,285]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Hippasteria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[288,422,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Hippasteria</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mah, C. L." box="[436,619,260,285]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="211 - 228" refId="ref72184" refString="Mah, C. L. (2015) New species, corallivory, in situ video observations and overview of the Goniasteridae (Valvatida, Asteroidea) in the Hawaiian Region. Zootaxa, 3926 (2), 211 - 228. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3926.2.3" type="journal article" year="2015">
Mah 
<emphasis box="[496,545,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, which displays a similar pattern throughout its range.
</paragraph>
